item.title: Cant Put Server Online
item.dc:creator: @coolguy12123 coolguy12123
item.description:
@coolguy12123 wrote:

Ok. Since your server is portfowarded, you need to put your server online. To put it online, you need to go to no-ip.org and sign up. After signing up, you need to add a host. For example: yourservername.no-ip.biz and download the special no-ip program. Make sure that you tick your host, and after you checked that your server is online, go on mediafire or other sites and upload the file

Now for the hard part. To make a webclient, you need to do is to “jar and sign your client”. Go to the “Server tutorials” and get the jarring info there
